The iron door has slammed shut, cutting off the rhythmic thunder of the Dread-Hooves. You stand in the courtyard of the Inner Ring, the air suddenly, unnervingly quiet. The Altar of Silence sits before you, a slab of marble that seems to pull the very heat from the air.

The three blindfolded Warden-Priests turn their heads toward you in perfect unison. One extends a hand toward the wooden sphere fused to Brother Thistle’s cooling flesh.

"The time for words has passed with the setting sun," the Priest intones. "The Seed is heavy with the memories of the dying. To wash it clean, you must leave a part of yourself in the basin. The Altar requires its due."

